Name: AccountCurrencyCode
Notes: The currency of the Customer account.

Name: AccountDescriptiveName
Notes: The descriptive name of the Customer account.

Name: AccountTimeZone
Notes: Name of the timezone selected for the Customer account. For example: "(GMT-05:00) Eastern Time". This field does not reflect the current state of daylight saving time for the timezone.

Name: AdGroupId
Notes: The ID of the AdGroup.

Name: AdGroupName
Notes: The name of the AdGroup.

Name: AdGroupStatus
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / unknown
ENABLED / enabled
PAUSED / paused
REMOVED / removed
Notes: Status of the ad group.

Name: AverageCpc
Notes: The total cost of all clicks divided by the total number of clicks received.

Name: AveragePosition
Notes: Your ad's position relative to those of other advertisers. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: CampaignId
Notes: The ID of the Campaign.

Name: CampaignName
Notes: The name of the Campaign.

Name: CampaignStatus
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / unknown
ENABLED / enabled
PAUSED / paused
REMOVED / removed
Notes: The status of the Campaign.

Name: Clicks
Notes: The number of clicks.

Name: CombinedAdsOrganicClicks
Notes: Clicks from ads or organic search results.

Name: CombinedAdsOrganicClicksPerQuery
Notes: CombinedAdsOrganicClicks divided by CombinedAdsOrganicQueries. This field is formatted with dot (".") for decimal separator, precision of two decimal positions and no thousands separator (e.g. 1000000.00). To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: CombinedAdsOrganicQueries
Notes: Total number of searches that returned pages from your site in the organic search results or triggered one of your ads.

Name: Ctr
Notes: The number of clicks your ad receives (Clicks) divided by the number of times your ad is shown (Impressions). Percentage returned as "x.xx%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: CustomerDescriptiveName
Notes: The descriptive name of the Customer.

Name: Date
Notes: The date formatted as yyyy-MM-dd.

Name: DayOfWeek
Enum Values:
MONDAY / Monday
TUESDAY / Tuesday
WEDNESDAY / Wednesday
THURSDAY / Thursday
FRIDAY / Friday
SATURDAY / Saturday
SUNDAY / Sunday
Notes: The name of the day of the week, e.g., "Monday".

Name: ExternalCustomerId
Notes: The Customer ID.

Name: Impressions
Notes: Count of how often your ad has appeared on a search results page or website on the Google Network.

Name: KeywordId
Notes: The ID of the Keyword that triggered the ad.

Name: KeywordTextMatchingQuery
Notes: Keyword that matched the query and triggered the ad.

Name: Month
Notes: The first day of the month, formatted as yyyy-MM-dd.

Name: MonthOfYear
Enum Values:
JANUARY / January
FEBRUARY / February
MARCH / March
APRIL / April
MAY / May
JUNE / June
JULY / July
AUGUST / August
SEPTEMBER / September
OCTOBER / October
NOVEMBER / November
DECEMBER / December
Notes: The name of the month of the year, e.g., "December".

Name: OrganicAveragePosition
Notes: Average top position of your organic listing (or multiple listings) for each query. This field is formatted with dot (".") for decimal separator, precision of two decimal positions and no thousands separator (e.g. 1000000.00). To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: OrganicClicks
Notes: Number of times someone clicked your site's listing in the unpaid results for a particular query.

Name: OrganicClicksPerQuery
Notes: Number of clicks youâ€™ve received on your organic search listings divided by the total number of searches that returned pages from your site. This field is formatted with dot (".") for decimal separator, precision of two decimal positions and no thousands separator (e.g. 1000000.00). To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: OrganicImpressions
Notes: Number of organic search listing impressions.

Name: OrganicImpressionsPerQuery
Notes: Average number of times a page from your site was listed per query. This field is formatted with dot (".") for decimal separator, precision of two decimal positions and no thousands separator (e.g. 1000000.00). To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: OrganicQueries
Notes: Total number of searches that returned organic search results for your site over the given period.

Name: PrimaryCompanyName
Notes: Company name of the account.

Name: Quarter
Notes: The first day of the quarter, formatted as yyyy-MM-dd. Uses the calendar year for quarters, e.g., the second quarter of 2014 starts on 2014-04-01.

Name: QueryMatchType
Enum Values:
AUTO / auto
BROAD / broad
EXACT / exact
EXPANDED / broad
PHRASE / phrase
Notes: Match type of the keyword that triggered the ad.

Name: SearchQuery
Notes: Query that led to the impression.

Name: SerpType
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / unknown
ADS_ONLY / Ad shown only
ORGANIC_ONLY / Organic shown only
ADS_AND_ORGANIC / Both shown
Notes: The type of search result.

Name: Week
Notes: The date for the Monday of the week, formatted as yyyy-MM-dd.

Name: Year
Notes: The year, formatted as yyyy.
